                    <p>‪During one of Dia’s first turf war matches, a power outage occurred, the first reporting of an incident like this. As she was splatted and about to respawn, the spawn point malfunctioned, causing her not to reappear even after the power was restored. At the realization, the match was cancelled, panic erupted from the spectators, and close ones rushed to the scene to see if their loved one was still present. The news crew stormed the scene, alongside skilled mechanics who knew how spawn points worked. Despite the hours they tried tampering with the spawn, nothing brought Dia back; they were at a complete loss and unfortunately had to call it quits and notify her family about her presumed death. As a result of the incident, the stage in question, Bluefin Depot, was shut down for public use, and abandoned.‬‬</p>
                    
                    <p>‪Months past before Dia reappeared from the spawn, and when she noticed she’s been freed, she also notices what’s happened to her body; her entire being is glitching in a pixelated mess, her voice distorted... In her panic she pops, proofing out of existence and returning her to the spawn point once again. This warping in and out of reality irregularly plagues Dia for years, tearing down her mental state significantly. She was lonely and afraid, afraid she’ll loop like this forever.‬</p>
            
